benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: DELETE /1.0/kb/invoicePayments/{paymentId}/tags - Remove tags from payment

covered: Valid Deletion scenarios: TC01-04 cover removing all tags, a single tagDef, multiple tagDefs, and header-influenced deletions.
No-tags case: TC05 ensures 204 with empty body when payment has no tags.
Comprehensive invalid input handling: TC06 (invalid paymentId), TC09 (invalid tagDef), TC13 (SQL injection attempt).
Non-existent payment handling: TC07 verifies 404 when paymentId not found.
Authorization and header checks: TC11 (401 for unauthorized) and TC08 (400 for missing X-Killbill-CreatedBy).
Error and downtime coverage: TC12 (503 service unavailable) and TC22 (504 timeout).
Query parameter robustness: TC02/TC03 (single/multiple tagDef), TC14 (extra query parameter).
Edge-case handling for tag not present: TC10 returns 204 with no change.
Scalability and performance: TC15 (large number of tagDef), TC17 (performance under load).
Concurrency and data integrity: TC16 (concurrent deletions) and TC21 (data consistency after removal).
Audit/logging and backward compatibility: TC20 (audit logs) and TC19 (backward compatibility).
Regression coverage: TC18 ensures previously fixed issue remains resolved.
gaps: Rate limiting/throttling tests to verify behavior under rapid or burst DELETE requests.
Caching behavior verification (ETag/Cache-Control) and related cache headers.
Internal Server Error (500) scenario beyond service unavailability.
Header content validation beyond presence (e.g., malformed X-Killbill-CreatedBy).
Observability and metrics coverage for server-side logs/metrics beyond audit logs.
recommendations: Add 403 Forbidden tests to cover insufficient privileges (not just unauthorized).
Add rate-limiting and throttling tests to assess behavior under high request volume.
Add caching header validations (ETag/Cache-Control) and verify caching behavior.
Add 500 Internal Server Error scenario to cover generic server failures beyond service unavailability.
Enhance header validation tests for malformed or unexpected header values (beyond missing).
Introduce targeted idempotency tests by repeating DELETE requests and validating consistent final state.
